<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,1341,1548]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1341,1368]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Having bipartite LO in 
<date box="[538,575,1342,1368]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">V7</date>
; the only species in this genus having both bipartite LO in 
<date box="[1225,1259,1342,1368]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">V7</date>
and pale brown dorsal colouration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,1341,1548]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1414,1440]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[324,403,1414,1440]" name="Vietnam" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Tonkin</collectingCountry>
(Vietnamese Bắc Kỳ) is the northernmost part of 
<collectingCountry box="[987,1097,1414,1440]" name="Vietnam" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Viet Nam</collectingCountry>
south of 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1405,1414,1440]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1450,1476]" name="China" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
and east of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[450,508,1450,1476]" name="Laos" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Laos</collectingCountry>
. This species is not further distinguished here apart from the key to males. However it is reliably assigned here and was identified clearly in the collection of the MNHN by Ballantyne in 2013 as having bipartite LO in 
<date box="[324,358,1522,1548]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">V7</date>
and an asymmetrical abdominal T8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
